# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ScreenBridge .gitignore
#
# Rule of thumb — ignore anything that is:
#   • GENERATED  (build output: target/, bin/, obj/, .build/, the header*)
#   • LOCAL      (per-machine / per-editor: IDE caches, .DS_Store, .claude/)
#   • SECRET     (keys, certs, .env)
# Keep anything that is SOURCE, or that PINS a build for reproducibility
#   (Cargo.lock, Package.resolved) — see the "do NOT ignore" notes below.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Development-only — never published (deliberate: the spec stays out of git)
/plans

## Local agent / tooling state (per-machine; not part of the product)
.claude/

## Secrets, certificates, keys — NEVER commit (PLAN.md §7, §14)
# ScreenBridge generates self-signed certs at runtime and stores them locally
# (TOFU); none of that belongs in version control.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.cer
*.crt
*.der
*.keystore
secrets.*

## Rust / cargo (core workspace)
/core/target/
**/*.rs.bk
# NOTE: core/Cargo.lock IS committed on purpose. The core ships a real binary
# artifact (the cdylib), so a pinned lockfile gives reproducible builds across
# machines and CI. Do NOT ignore it.

## Generated C ABI header
# NOTE: include/screenbridge.h is intentionally tracked so editors and the apps
# have it without a prior core build. It is regenerated deterministically by
# `cargo build` (core/crates/ffi/build.rs); do NOT ignore it.

## Swift / SPM / Xcode (macOS app)
/apps/macos/.build/
/apps/macos/.swiftpm/
DerivedData/
*.xcuserstate
**/xcuserdata/
# NOTE: apps/macos/Package.resolved should be committed once SPM deps exist
# (it pins their exact versions). Do NOT ignore it.

## .NET / MSBuild (Windows app)
**/bin/
**/obj/
.vs/
*.user
*.suo
*.binlog
[Tt]est[Rr]esults/
*.trx
*.nupkg

## WinUI / MSIX packaging output (appears from Phase 5 onward)
**/AppPackages/
**/BundleArtifacts/
*.appx
*.appxbundle
*.appxupload
*.msix
*.msixbundle
*.msixupload
*.msi
GeneratedArtifacts/
_pkginfo.txt

## Editors / IDEs (per-developer; un-ignore a specific shared file if needed)
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~

## Transient logs (commit deliberate measurement results under docs/, not as *.log)
*.log

## OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
